text: The Yukagir Mammoth is a frozen male woolly mammoth found in 2002 in northern Yakutia and is an exceptional discovery. It is named after the village of Yukagir near where it was found. == Related pages == * Yuka (mammoth) * Lyuba (mammoth) * List of mammoth specimens == References == Category:Mummies Category:Proboscideans
